# RentACar Backend - Environment Variables

## Spring Profile (dev or prod)
SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE=dev

# Database Configuration
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=rentacar
DB_USERNAME=rentacar_user
DB_PASSWORD=your_secure_password

# JWT Configuration
JWT_SECRET=your-secret-key-min-256-bits-long-change-this-in-production
JWT_EXPIRATION=86400000

# MAIL_PORT=587
# MAIL_USERNAME=your-email@example.com
# MAIL_PASSWORD=your-email-password

### Optional - File Storage
# STORAGE_TYPE=local
# STORAGE_LOCAL_PATH=/var/rentacar/uploads
# AWS_S3_BUCKET=rentacar-files
# AWS_REGION=eu-central-1

## Setup Instructions

1. Copy this file to `.env` in the project root
2. Update all values with your actual credentials
3. Never commit `.env` to version control
4. For production, use a secrets manager (AWS Secrets Manager, HashiCorp Vault, etc.)
